# System Architecture Overview

The Primed HIE Core follows a modular, API-first architecture:

- Patient Identity Layer: Generates and manages unique patient IDs
- Interoperability Layer: Handles data exchange between facilities
- Application Layer: Supports registration, appointments, and referrals
- Offline Sync Engine: Enables operation in low-connectivity environments
- Integration Layer: Connects to existing hospital systems

The system is designed for scalability, multi-tenancy, and deployment across multiple healthcare environments.
